ace%2C%20very%20few%20Zilla%20Parishad%20schools%20have%20access%20to%20engaging%2C%20age-appropriate%20English%20reading%20material.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%E2%80%99s%20where%20%3Cem%3ES%20for%20Schools%3C%2Fem%3E%20stepped%20in%20with%20a%20deceptively%20simple%20model%3A%20five%20schools%20per%20cluster%2C%2050%20carefully%20curated%20books%20per%20school%2C%20rotated%20every%20six%20months.%20All%20books%20are%20donated%2C%20and%20everything%20%E2%80%94%20from%20transport%20to%20installation%20%E2%80%94%20is%20managed%20by%20volunteers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20impact%20was%20immediate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20ZP%20School%20Gherewadi%2C%20where%20one%20of%20the%20first%20libraries%20was%20set%20up%2C%20teacher%20Babasaheb%20Kale%20still%20remembers%20the%20children%E2%80%99s%20surprise.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20completely%20new%20to%20them%20%E2%80%94%20having%20books%20with%20colours%2C%20characters%2C%20and%20stories.%20But%20they%20took%20to%20it%20naturally.%20Most%20of%20the%20students%20wanted%20to%20read%20more.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVaishali%20Wadettawar%2C%20a%20teacher%20at%20ZP%20School%20Ghodhpeth%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F248245%2Fmohammed-dilawar-sparrow-conservation-activist-nasik-nature-india-nursery-native-plant-species-city-forests-indigenous-gop94%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMaharashtra%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fa%3EChandrapur%2C%20happily%20notes%2C%20%E2%80%9CStudents%20can%20now%20make%20sentences%20in%20English%20with%20the%20help%20of%20a%20word%20or%20an%20object%20%E2%80%94%20this%20is%20a%20part%20of%20their%20curriculum.%20Earlier%2C%20they%20needed%20help%20with%20vocabulary%2C%20but%20now%20they%20manage%20without%20anyone%E2%80%99s%20assistance.%20Even%20Class%204%20students%20are%20able%20to%20hold%20basic%20English%20conversations.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EBuilding%20confidence%20through%20language