osteosarcoma%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202000.%20She%20was%2025%20when%20she%20died%20in%20hospice%20in%202001.%20I%20was%20with%20her%20when%20she%20took%20her%20last%20breath.%20Hearing%20%26quot%3Bcancer%26quot%3B%20again%2C%20this%20time%20about%20my%20mom%2C%20reopened%20every%20wound%20I%20had%20tried%20to%20heal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20mom%20lives%20in%20Georgia%20with%20my%20oldest%20sister.%20I%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftraveled-america-finding-best-us-city-live-in-tucson-arizona-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elive%20in%20Arizona%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20almost%202%2C000%20miles%20away.%20The%20very%20next%20day%2C%20on%20July%204th%2C%20after%20my%20mom%20told%20me%20about%20the%20diagnosis%2C%20I%20flew%20to%20Georgia.%20I%20needed%20to%20see%20and%20be%20there%20with%20my%20mom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2209f99068-f6e1-41c5-be99-15c4b832cb71%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ECancer%20treatment%20began%2C%20but%20dementia%20changed%20everything%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20mom%20began%20treatment%2C%20radiation%2C%20and%20chemotherapy%20about%20four%20weeks%20after%20she%20was%20diagnosed%20with%20cancer.%20My%20sister%20quickly%20became%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flessons-learned-end-of-life-planning-when-mother-died-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eprimary%20caregiver%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20taking%20my%20mom%20to%20her%20treatment%20appointments%20and%20taking%20care%20of%20things%20around%20the%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20grateful%2C%20but%20also%20felt%20the%20pressure%20of%20not%20always%20being%20there.%20I%20started%20to%20visit%20more%20frequently%20%E2%80%94%20at%20least%20once%20a%20month%20for%20a%20week%20at%20a%20time%2C%20and%20during%20one%20visit%20for%20two%20weeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESix%20months%20after%20the%20cancer%20treatment%20began%2C%20we%20received%20another%20devastating%20diagnosis%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Falzheimers-vs-dementia%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edementia%3C%2Fa%3E.%20She%20had%20been%20forgetting%20things%20and%20asking%20the%20same%20questions%20repeatedly.%20Sometimes%20she%20would%20hallucinate%2C%20convinced%20people%20were%20in%20the%20room%20who%20weren't%20there.%20It%20was%20scary%20to%20think%20that%20she%20might%20not%20recognize%20me%20or%20my%20siblings%20someday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDementia%20added%20an%20entirely%20new%20dimension%20to%20her%20care.%20I%20worried%20not%20just%20about%20her%20health%2C%20but%20whether%20she'd%20even%20remember%20I%20had%20come.%20I%20stayed%20for%20two%20weeks%20during%20one%20visit%2C%20helping%20with%20appointments%20and%20daily%20care%2C%20trying%20to%20be%20present%20however%20I%20could.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d1c91f27-f4f6-4985-bf0b-b2867063738f%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EEach%20time%20I%20returned%20to%20Arizona%2C%20I%20carried%20guilt%20with%20me%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20mom%20raised%20me%20and%20my%20siblings%20mostly%20on%20her%20own.%20She%20was%20always%20there.%20She%20never%20missed%20any%20of%20my%20big%20events%20in%20life%2C%20whether%20joyful%20or%20painful.%20From%20graduating%20from%20high%20school%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-command-that-okays-military-recruits-approaching-crisis-point-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emilitary%20training%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%201989%2C%20to%20graduating%20from%20college%20in%201996%2C%20to%20my%20first%20wife's%20death%20in%202001%2C%20she's%20been%20there%20for%20everything.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20now%2C%20I%20wasn't%20close%20when%20she%20needed%20me%20the%20most.%20I%20couldn't%20stop%20by%20or%20take%20over%20when%20my%20sister%20needed%20a%20break.%20Distance%20made%20everything%20feel%20heavier%3B%20every%20phone%20call%20was%20more%20urgent%2C%20and%20every%20visit%20was%20more%20emotional.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20visiting%20monthly.%20It%20wasn't%20perfect%2C%20but%20it%20was%20something.%20Since%20working%20remotely%2C%20I%20have%20scheduled%20my%20visits%20around%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbusiness-travel-policies-avoid-burnout-work-trip-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebusiness%20travel%20commitments%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20couldn't%20always%20be%20there%2C%20but%20I%20could%20be%20consistent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESoon%20after%2C%20tensions%20started%20to%20build%20between%20my%20siblings.%20Conversations%20about%20what%20would%20happen%20with%20the%20house%20or%20other%20assets%20if%20my%20mom%20died%20became%20more%20frequent.%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20argue.%20I%20told%20them%20clearly%3A%20I%20don't%20care%20about%20the%20possessions.%20As%20far%20as%20I%20was%20concerned%2C%20they%20could%20have%20everything%2C%20and%20I%20told%20them%20so.%20I%20just%20wanted%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20my%20mom%20was%20taken%20care%20of.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2246970c60-5da2-418d-b98c-5a4fdae527d7%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ETime%20is%20everything%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20moment%20that%20stays%20with%20me%20happened%20during%20a%20quiet%20day.%20My%20mom%20was%20sitting%20in%20her%20recliner.%20I%20don't%20remember%20what%20she%20said%20or%20if%20she%20said%20anything%20at%20all.%20I%20kneeled%20beside%20her%2C%20hugged%20her%2C%20and%20began%20to%20cry.%20There%20were%20no%20big%20words.%20I%20was%20just%20a%20son%20holding%20his%20mom%20and%20trying%20to%20take%20the%20moment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20learned%20that%20caregiving%20isn't%20just%20about%20being%20in%20the%20same%20zip%20code.%20It's%20about%20presence%2C%20consistency%2C%20and%20love.%20Sometimes%2C%20it's%20a%20plane%20ride%2C%20sometimes%20it's%20a%20call%2C%20and%20sometimes%20it's%20just%20sitting%20quietly%20in%20the%20same%20room.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20hasn't%20been%20easy%2C%20but%20it%20has%20reminded%20me%20that%20when%20someone%20you%20love%20is%20slipping%20away%2C%20you%20don't%20cling%20to%20things%3B%20you%20hold%20on%20to